# 2. 今日も練習！

KAITO: Then, let's get started!
Kohane: Okay! Thank you for agreeing to help us again today!
Kohane: ♪————! ————!!
KAITO: Yes, excellent start! Try to keep that up!
KAITO: (She sounds very motivated again today.)
KAITO: (She seems to have a clear image of how she wants her voice to be heard.)
Kohane: (We've made our decision! This is our new starting point!)
Kohane: (Which means...)
Kohane: (I have to remember what I felt... During our third event, and when we faced off against Taiga...!)
Kohane: ♪————!!
Luka: Oh wow. Looks like Kohane's bringing her A game!
Luka: So, Akito, why don't we try to do the same?
Akito: Yes. Let's do just that.
Luka: Okay! Here we go!
Toya: He's singing with a lot of power... I need to do the same.
MEIKO: Hehe. I know how you feel. So, why don't we also get started?
MEIKO: Rin, Len! Could you lend me a hand again?
Rin: Of course!
MEIKO: I want you to pay close attention to how these two sing. Think about where they expend energy or refrain and try to recreate that.
Toya: Okay, I'll do just that! Thank you both for doing this.
Len: Yeah, no problem! Ready?!
Rin & Len: ♪————!
Toya: ♪————!
An & Miku: ♪————! ————!!
An: There... I fell behind you again, Miku...
An: But I'm not done yet...! Let's go one more time!
Miku: Hehe. That's the spirit. I'll go as many times as you want.
Kohane: (Everyone sounds really motivated...)
Kohane: (There's no point in thinking about that. I have to focus on what I'm doing now... I need to do much more...!)
Kohane & An: Huff... Huff... Huff...
Akito & Toya: Huff... Huff...
Miku: Nice work, everyone. But I'm starting to hear fatigue in your voices.
KAITO: So am I. It's getting late, so why don't we call things here for now? We wouldn't want your families to worry.
Akito: Right...
An: Whoa, it is getting late... I gotta get home!
Kohane: M-Me too...
Kohane: (But...)
Kohane: I want to keep practicing...
Miku: Kohane, you shouldn't push yourself so hard. Overdoing it is only going to backfire.
KAITO: She's right. Knowing when to take breaks is also important.
Kohane: Yes, you're both right...
Toya: Anyway, MEIKO, thank you very much for letting us borrow your cafe again.
MEIKO: Of course. It's always my pleasure.
Akito: We'll see you all again tomorrow.
Toya: Hm...?
An: Toya? What's up?
Toya: Oh, so... Soma, Tono's partner... He just sent me a message...
Kohane: What do you think Soma's like...?
Akito: Oh, that's right. You two haven't met him yet.
An: No, we never got a chance to go with Arata to the hospital since stuff kept coming up.
Toya: As for what Soma is like... He's...
Toya: Friendly, easy to talk to...and clearly loves music very much.
Toya: I'm sure you two will also enjoy meeting him.
Kohane: Oh, that's good to hear...
Kohane: I was a little worried since we're coming along on such short notice. But I'm really excited now.
An: Me too. Also...
An: I hope we can find out how Arata's doing. Soma might still be in contact with him.
Kohane: Right... It'll be nice to sit down and talk with him.
Young Local Musicians: Oh, hey. Isn't that Vivid BAD SQUAD...?
Young Local Musicians: Didn't Taiga totally demolish them the other day?
Young Local Musicians: Yeah, everyone's been talking about that battle. Winning in style's one thing, but that was pretty mean of him...
Young Local Musicians: I really thought they had a chance against him. Guess this means no one's ever gonna surpass RAD WEEKEND.
Kohane: (Oh...)
An: No one's ever gonna surpass RAD WEEKEND, huh...?
An: Yeah, of course they'd think that... I mean, there was just that big of a skill gap between us and Uncle Taiga...
Akito: Yeah...
Toya: In any case, let's go... We don't have time for this right now.
Kohane: Okay...
Young Local Musicians: I mean, this is sorta what they get for going around saying they're gonna surpass RAD WEEKEND.
Young Local Musicians: I know, right? Did they really think that they could become even more legendary than Taiga and his team?
Owner of Crawl Green: Hey.
Owner of Crawl Green: You kids get your kicks laughing at the people who try?
Young Local Musicians: Huh? You talkin' to us, gramps?
Young Local Musicians: Crap...! That's the owner of Crawl Green!
Young Local Musicians: What?! We, uhh...! W-We're sorry!!!
Owner of Crawl Green: *Sigh*
Owner of COL: ... I'm guessing you heard from Ken?
Owner of Crawl Green: Yeah, he said he told them everything.
Owner of Crawl Green: I guess this is it... About time we all got our comeuppance, eh?
Owner of Crawl Green: Nagi's wishes were just part of it. We put a whole lot on An's shoulders.
Owner of COL: We did...
Owner of Crawl Green: You know...
Owner of Crawl Green: I feel awful about what we did to her. At the same time...
Owner of Crawl Green: If An has come to terms with Nagi's last wishes... I can't help but feel excited...
Owner of COL: ...
Owner of COL: There isn't much us old folks can do for her and her friends. We should stand aside and let them walk down the path they've chosen...
Owner of Crawl Green: Yeah, I agree...
An: *Sigh* No gawkers here. I think we're far enough away now.
Akito: I guess everyone really is talking about our battle against Taiga...
Kohane: Huh...?
Kohane: Oh...! Isn't that...?
An: Kotaro...!
